K. Specialized Safety Features

Site specific detection and control equipment (safety features) are deployed throughout the plant to:
1. Contain/control a release;
2. Quickly detect a release; and
3. Reduce the consequences of an RMP-regulated substance release.

The following type of safety features are used in the covered processes:
1. Release Detection
   a. Hydrocarbon and hydrogen sulfide detectors with alarms.
2. Release Containment/Control
   a. Process relief valves that discharge to a flare to capture and incinerate episodic releases;
   b. Automated and manual valves to isolate the process;
   c. Automated plant shutdown system to shut down all engines, plant utilities, and automatically operate all automatic valves to their fail-safe position, diverting all incoming gas to the emergency flare;
   d. Curbing or diking to contain liquids releases;
   e. Redundant equipment and instrumentation; and
   f. Atmospheric relief devices.
3. Release Mitigation
   a. Fire suppression and extinguishing system;
   b. Trained emergency response personnel;
   c. Personal protective equipment; and
   d. Blast-resistant building to help protect control systems and personnel.

L. FIVE YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY

The Caymus Natural Gas Processing Facility has had no RMP-reportable accident during the past five years. 

M. EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM INFORMATION

The plant maintains a written emergency response plan, which is in place to help protect employee and public safety as well as the environment. The plan identifies steps to be taken in case of an accidental release including:
1. Proper first aid and medical treatment for exposures;
2. Evacuation plans and accounting for personnel after an evacuation;

